# Iteration 9 - keep - score: 0.9567
Operation: REWORD
Reasoning: The dominant errors are still boundary and omission issues around decisions, especially committed implementation/tooling choices being missed while descriptive labels or architecture summaries are over-extracted. I chose REWORD because the current rule already covers decisions, but its phrasing is too broad and lets in naming/description statements while not clearly treating agreed implementation choices as decisions. I rejected ADD because recent history shows additions and similar boundary-focused rewords were discarded, and a tighter replacement of the existing extraction-boundary rule is the single highest-impact change without increasing prompt length.

- - Treat items as extractable only when they are stated as concrete project state: tasks are assigned, planned, in-progress, blocked, or completed work items; decisions are explicit agreements or adopted choices that set approach, scope, policy, or tooling; people are named individuals with their stated role or responsibility wording; project owner is the person stated as owning the project or product side. Do not extract project names, background descriptions, role statements as tasks, implementation details that merely explain how something works, milestone goals or desired outcomes, conditional next steps, or possible future ideas as tasks or decisions.
+ - Treat items as extractable only when they are stated as concrete project state: tasks are assigned, planned, in-progress, blocked, or completed work items; decisions are explicit agreements or adopted choices, including committed implementation, tooling, format, scope, or policy choices that the team will use; people are named individuals with their stated role or responsibility wording; project owner is the person stated as owning the project or product side. Do not extract project names, temporary labels, background descriptions, role statements as tasks, implementation details that only describe how something works without an adopted choice, milestone goals or desired outcomes, conditional next steps, or possible future ideas as tasks or decisions.
